CPF database layout note
========================

This file is a short reference only.
The executable installation scripts are under specs/sql.

Canonical install scripts
-------------------------

- specs/sql/00_all_install.sql
- specs/sql/00_all_install_and_smoke.sql

Database ownership
------------------

- pfwDB: framework-owned metadata and common reference tables.
  - TRAN_LOG
  - TRAN_LOG_DTL
  - code_table
  - message_table
  - response_code_table
  - config_table
  - cache_refresh_event
  - file_exchange_log
  - security_jwt_key
  - security_token_audit_log
- admDB: admin console, operator, role, menu, audit, dynamic log rules.
- accDB: account sample domain. Uses acc_account.
- mbrDB: member sample domain. Uses member.

cmnDB is intentionally not used.
CMN is a common Java module, not a separate data owner. Framework/common
reference data belongs to pfwDB.

All CPF-owned tables must include:

- created_by
- created_at
- updated_by
- updated_at

Use specs/sql/99_smoke_check.sql after installation to verify the layout.
